The DeHub in-browser video editor (src/pages/Editor.tsx and src/components/editor/*,
src/store/editorStore.ts, src/lib/editor/*) is adapted from OpenCut
(https://github.com/OpenCut-app/OpenCut), an open-source video editor released
under the MIT license. Architectural ideas (editor shell with top bar, media
library, preview, and timeline; client-side media store; per-clip thumbnails)
are derived from that project. No OpenCut source code is copied verbatim — the
implementation has been re-written natively for this Vite + React + shadcn
stack.

